track_notes:
Up the ridge from Watchman Overlook. Scrambled to the summit from the north side. 
For the descent I scrambled the way I came up and headed down the scree to join the trail.

Started the hike by following the PCT\Rim Trail around to the north. Proceeded diagonally across the slope till I reached the ridge-line and then followed that up. Left my pack and poles at the ledge below the summit block to have less gear and free hands for the scramble to the top.

N7UN and I descended this route and it seemed the easier than our choice for ascent. If I go back I will go up this route too. PCT to a wash/drainage, walk up and path to the left towards rocks. We only went to a safe AZ location.
